Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

A map of the island nation of Sri Lanka can be found at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/srilanka.pdf>. - Mod.LL]

[In the prior ProMED-mail posting on leptospirosis in Sri Lanka (see
Leptospirosis - Sri Lanka (04) 20080909.2810) there had been 118
deaths and 3960 cases reported during the period 1 Jan 2008 through
the end of August 2008 (compared with 34 deaths and 2195 cases
reported in 2007). In the above newswire there are reports of an
additional 33 deaths and 675 cases reported since the end of August
2008 - a significant increase -- suggesting that this year's rainy
season probably resulted in more areas with local flooding of the
paddy areas of the country. - Mod.MPP]
